    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:1.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:2.1",
          "pli": "“‘Rāgavinayo dosavinayo mohavinayo’ti, bhante, vuccati. ",
          "en": "“Sir, they speak of ‘the removal of greed, hate, and delusion’. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:2.2",
          "pli": "Kissa nu kho etaṃ, bhante, adhivacanaṃ: ",
          "en": "What is this a term for?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:2.3",
          "pli": "‘rāgavinayo dosavinayo mohavinayo’”ti? ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:2.4",
          "pli": "“Nibbānadhātuyā kho etaṃ, bhikkhu, adhivacanaṃ: ",
          "en": "“Mendicant, the removal of greed, hate, and delusion is a term for the natural principle of extinguishment. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:2.5",
          "pli": "‘rāgavinayo dosavinayo mohavinayo’ti. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:2.6",
          "pli": "Āsavānaṃ khayo tena vuccatī”ti. ",
          "en": "It’s used to speak of the ending of defilements.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ vutte, so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "When he said this, the mendicant said to the Buddha: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.2",
          "pli": "“‘amataṃ, amatan’ti, bhante, vuccati. ",
          "en": "“Sir, they speak of ‘the deathless’. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.3",
          "pli": "Katamaṃ nu kho, bhante, amataṃ, katamo amatagāmimaggo”ti? ",
          "en": "What is the deathless? And what is the path that leads to the deathless?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.4",
          "pli": "“Yo kho, bhikkhu, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—",
          "en": "“The ending of greed, hate, and delusion. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.5",
          "pli": "idaṃ vuccati amataṃ. ",
          "en": "This is called the deathless. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.6",
          "pli": "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo amatagāmimaggo, seyyathidaṃ—",
          "en": "The path that leads to the deathless is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.7",
          "pli": "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhī”ti. ",
          "en": "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.7:3.8",
          "pli": "Sattamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
